<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>Well, it's that time of the year again, full of extravagance and over-indulgence.</p><p>I have momentarily emerged from my alcoholic-blurred state, to put up some new content that has been submitted. I will have to be brief, as I feel a desire to go talk to god on the great white porcelain telephone.</p><p>We have a new picture in the <a href="/humour/index.asp">humour section</a>, a new file in the <a href="/equipment/index.asp">equipment section</a> and a new <a href="/quests/index.asp">quest guide.</a> The new articles are at the bottom of each page.</p><p>One last comment before I go, when making submissions, PLEASE do not use html editors or word processors to add in the content to the template I provide. It takes me 10 times as long to strip out all the rubbish they add to the code than it would to just type it out from scratch. I was sent a wonderful story that unfortunately has MS Word encoding all over it, and I simply cant be bothered to strip it all out.</p><p>If you don't know how to use a text editor to work with an html file, then please just submit it as plain text, and let me do the work, saves me a lot of time in the long run.</p></FONT></ul>

